Interface ClusterSplitHandler<C extends java.lang.Comparable<C>,​T>

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ClusterSplitHandler<C extends java.lang.Comparable<C>,​T>
    A callback that is invoked when an already existing cluster is split up during the Clustering of (online) deduplication.

        boolean clusterSplit​(@NonNull
                     @NonNull Cluster<C,​T> mainCluster,
                     @NonNull
                     @NonNull java.util.List<Cluster<C,​T>> splitParts)
        Invoked when an already existing cluster is split up during the Clustering of (online) deduplication.

        The cluster split handle may give a veto by returning false, which the clustering may or may not use.

        Returns:
        false if this handler would like to leave the cluster in-place.

        Checks if the given set of clusters contains more than element and invokes clusterSplit(Cluster, List).
        Parameters:
        clusters - the clusters resulting from the latest Clustering invocation.
        newRecord - the new record triggering the clustering.
        Returns:
